summary: okay so i noticed that cyrus goes to the principals office clearly to talk to dr metcalf about the gun situation. when he walks...
body:
okay so i noticed that cyrus goes to the principals office clearly to talk to dr metcalf about the gun situation. when he walks in he looks shocked to see the police officer already there which makes the “did something happen?” make more sense than it did before. but that leaves us with the police being there before cyrus even talked about what’s going on to the principal?

so either

1. cyrus called in advance

or

2. cyrus leaving made tj click into place and realise he has to speak up about the gun because if they were caught he probably wouldn’t be allowed at school for the cafeteria scene.

this would also be a good lead to the cafeteria scene because i’m assuming they hadn’t seen each other since cyrus left the dirt bike situation.

you can see in the photos he’s gone to see the principal and he looks shocked that the police are there?

summary: Hi! Where's your theory on tj's internalized homophobia?
question: Hi! Where's your theory on tj's internalized homophobia?
answer:
hello my friend, thank you for asking! 

I have this theory that TJ’s dad may be either very distant or even emotionally abusive. it would makes a lot of sense particularly in the context of the way he treated Buffy. a closeted gay boy who is able to grip on to a show of traditional masculinity like excelling at sports as his only connection to an emotionally abusive or distant father. this connection is suddenly threatened by, god forbid, a girl who is not only better than him at the symbol of his masculinity but also shines a direct light on his academic difficulties in the classic Buffy way that can come across as incredibly harsh and arrogant at times. so TJ lashes out until he realizes that his relationship with Cyrus can’t go anywhere until he makes peace with Buffy. his priorities shift from protecting his relationship with his father to protecting his relationship with Cyrus.

for me as well this fits with a TJ who would cave to peer pressure even when he’s clearly extremely uncomfortable/ashamed. he would have an incredibly deep seeded need to be seen as tough and cool and he’d be really scared to do anything to upset that perception. just like with his antagonism towards Buffy, I expect that he will reflect, regret what he’s done and his relationship with Cyrus will end up being his first priority again.

summary: Within the span of a week I went from freaking out about the promo, being depressed about Tyrus not becoming canon yet, thankful...
body:
Within the span of a week I went from freaking out about the promo, being depressed about Tyrus not becoming canon yet, thankful that we’re at least getting more content for them, then convinced that Tyrus wasn’t even going to happen (thanks Josh), then angry, then freaking out about the new promo/gun storyline, then sad about the likelihood of Tyrus becoming canon at all, then cautiously optimistic about what’s going to happen, and excited as hell for these episodes.

I love this show sm even if it continually messes with my emotions.

Within the span of a week I went from freaking out about the promo, being depressed about Tyrus not becoming canon yet, thankful that we’re at least getting more content for them, then convinced that Tyrus wasn’t even going to happen (thanks Josh), then angry, then freaking out about the new promo/gun storyline, then sad about the likelihood of Tyrus becoming canon at all, then cautiously optimistic about what’s going to happen, and excited as hell for these episodes.

I love this show sm even if it continually messes with my emotions.
